menu "Virtual UART Configuration"

    config VUART_CDC_DEBUG_PORT
        bool "Dedicate one CDC port to ESP debug console"
        default y
        help
            When enabled, one USB CDC-ACM port is used for ESP-IDF
            console output (ESP_LOG, printf, etc.) instead of being
            available for virtual UART routing.

            Disable this for production to make all CDC ports available
            for data routing.

    config VUART_CDC_DEBUG_INDEX
        int "CDC port index used for debug console (0 or 1)"
        depends on VUART_CDC_DEBUG_PORT
        range 0 1
        default 0
        help
            Which CDC-ACM port to use as the debug console.
            0 = CDC0 (first virtual COM port)
            1 = CDC1 (second virtual COM port)

endmenu
